description:
&lt;p&gt;KCHFT is a great place to work - but don’t just take our word for it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In our most recent report the CQC rated us as ‘outstanding’; and said:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff felt supported, valued and respected&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;They felt proud to work for the trust and were committed to the vision and values of the organisation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;There are high levels of staff satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff are proud of the organisation as a place to work and spoke highly of the culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are the only major NHS provider in the South East to be rated as ‘outstanding’, and one of only three community providers in the UK to have the highest rating; so why not join us? #cometocommunity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you enjoy providing evidence based care within a busy and friendly environment then this is the job for you.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We have this exciting opportunity for you to join our friendly, supportive knowledgeable multidisciplinary team working across both the Minor Injury unit at Edenbridge Memorial Hospital and the Sevenoaks UTC at Sevenoaks Hospital. You would be providing excellent care within your scope of practice, in line with the unit guidelines and policies of Kent Community Health Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Band 7 Emergency or Advanced Nurse Practitioner /Advanced or Emergency Care Practitioner. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You must have the relevant professional registration as; Nurse (NMC) or Paramedic (HPC) with evidence of service and role appropriate post registration study /qualifications and experience, including working in any of these following clinical areas:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Primary Care / GP service&lt;br /&gt;Urgent Care/ Ambulance Service as a Practitioner&lt;br /&gt;Accident &amp; Emergency&lt;br /&gt;Minor Injuries/ Illness Units / Walk in Centre&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will also need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of supplying medications under PGD’s&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of: working autonomously&lt;br /&gt;Evidence of team leadership&lt;br /&gt;Evidence of teaching and assessing others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working within a multi-disciplinary team&lt;br /&gt;Red dot Radiology Course/ IRMER&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on the &lt;strong&gt;17th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt; via Microsoft Teams. You will also receive a call after the advert closes to have a chat about your aspirations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from all groups in the community and will accommodate needs and make adjustments wherever possible. We welcome applications from individuals from diverse backgrounds and those covered by the Equalities Act.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameHayley MerrallsTelephone number07342701169&lt;/p&gt;
